<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/100.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister at
                                    Mexico City</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American Vice Consul in charge Guadalajara reports that in default
                            payment special tax ten thousand pesos authorities threaten attachment
                            property Compañía Galletera Nacional, stock of which is almost entirely
                            American owned.</p>
                        <p>Please request appropriate authorities to order withdrawal of demand for
                            payment this tax which appears to be an extraordinary special tax not
                            general and uniform in operation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>